headline.main: THE GREAT SHOWMAN DEAD; LAST HOURS OF THE LIFE OF PHINEAS T. BARNUM. THE VETERAN MANAGER SINKS INTO A PEACEFUL SLEEP THAT KNOWS NO WAKING -- THE FUNERAL TO BE PRIVATE AT HIS EXPRESS DESIRE.

snippet: BRIDGEPORT, Conn., April 7. -- At 6:22 o'clock to-night the long sickness of P.T. Barnum came to an end by his quietly passing away at Marina, his residence in this city.
